caption: Best Polish pierogi ever.
Hands down, one of the best meals in NYC.

Meat pierogies. Don’t bother with any other kind. If you like doughy giant pierogies you’ll like these. $15 but ridiculously filling plate of fairly authentic polish dumplings. I work in the Polish neighborhood of Greenpoint but don’t live there so if I have a craving these hit the spot.

I absolutely loved my meal and experience at Pierogi Boys tonight. I had half of the potato and cheese and the other half was the meat pierogi’s. Literally so yummy. Hours after my meal I still feel at home. The owner was so welcoming and had great conversation with me and another customer throughout our meal. I was planning on getting my meal to go but I am so glad that I stayed!

The guy who works here was super friendly and warm. He made us feel welcomed. I ordered the potato and cheese pierogis and they tasted amazing! The guy asked us if the food tastes good. I really appreciated him asking us this because even though he was busy taking orders from other customers, he still cared to make sure we were satisfied with the food. I was more than satisfied with the food and customer service. Everyone who reads this, must make it a point to stop here when you’re visiting Dekalb Market!

I’m Ukrainian and I cook borsch at home. I can assure that this place has a “home-taste” borsch.  The price is low compared to efforts that are put in cooking this not simple dish. I love love love Pierogi Boys. Great quality for an affordable price.

After my mama’s pierogis, these are the best pierogis I’ve had. I tried the sauerkraut and wild mushroom ones and they did not disappoint. Soft and full of flavor with every bite, exactly what a pierog should be like. Great place!

The best Pierogi in NYC! Such delicious filling flavors and perfect dough. The seasoning inside the potato and cheese is wonderful and the onions are so succulent. The service is exceptional and it is fun to watch the pierogi being made. Hands down one of my top favorites out of any restaurant in any city!

Excellent Perogi’s inside this cool mall! I had the platter which included a taste of everything and they were all fantastic! I really liked the cheese and potato perogi but you can’t go wrong with any of them. I think this is one of the best options within this mall and would highly recommend!

Possibly the best pierogis I've eaten outside of churches or homemade by my family. If you love meat, the sampler is a killer option. Not only is their a meat filled pierogi (my least favourite, but still pretty solid), but there are little chunks of sausage/bacon throughout. I prefer just sour cream and dill, but I think the addition of meat really makes the platter distinct and filling. I found the potato and cheese a tad lumpy. Prefer them more creamy, but again, the addition of meat really covered that taste. Very friendly service and cute artwork make this an easy 5 for me.

Fantastic pierogi sampler. Comes with sour cream and bacon chunks. Fantastically smooth and creamy pierogis. Loved them.

Really good boiled pierogies. I tried this place because I saw Andy Milonakis go here a couple weeks ago on his stream and I'm glad I did. These pierogies are boiled instead of traditionally being fried, and they taste delicious. I got the potato and cheese and everything tasted so fresh. The caramelized onions on top were a nice addition, and the sour cream as a dip made it even better. Now I know how bad the frozen pierogies I make at home are.  The price is a little crazy tbh ($13 and some change), but I'm still glad I had it.

To say that I arrived at their booth a hungry zombie and left a happy human being is an understatement. I got the potato pierogis and they were warm, hearty, flavorful, homemade deliciousness. The pierogi dough is so good and the filling is flavorful and simple. I watched a woman make the pierogi dough by hand. The service was excellent. The man working the bar made time for everyone, was friendly and engaging. I will definitely be back!! Great date spot!
The potato and cheese pierogi's are everything I dream of and more in a pierogi or just from life in general. Nothing needed other than what it comes with....amazing.

Friendly, they will help you navigate this heart, rib sticking, and filling goodie. The condiments are great also, a beet relish, sour cream (a must), and a hearty mustard for the kielbasa which was great. They have a combo, including meat filled ones, but the classics are great in itself. You can get kielbasa as a meal or add it as a side to the pierogis.

A very cool spot to satisfy your cravings for homemade pierogies, little flavor bombs of potato, cheese and meat wrapped in a blanket of doughy goodness. Ideal for take out , or sit around the small bar for a dose of comfort food!
